    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Quilts in which the pattern is organized in strips running the length of the quilt. May consist only of unpieced strips, or of unpieced strips alternating with pieced strips.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000004131/Brackman, comp., Encyclopedia of Pieced Quilt Patterns (1979)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Edredón en que el modelo es organizado en tiras a lo largo del largo de la colcha. Puede consistir sólo de pedazos de tiras o de pedazos de tira alternando con tiras enteras.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Quilts waarbij het patroon is opgebouwd uit stroken die over de lengte van de quilt lopen. Ze kunnen bestaan uit ononderbroken stroken of ononderbroken stroken afgewisseld door onderbroken stroken. Geen Nederlands equivalent.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>以長條布的花樣排列拼接而成的拼布被。可能包含未拼縫在一起的長條碎布，或者是已拼縫與未拼縫的長條碎布交錯。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
